def: A sweating; a profuse or morbid sweating, often succeeded by aneruption of small pimples.
Capable of being modified; liable to modification.
A genus of marine gastropods having a long, tapering spire.They belong to the Toxoglossa. Called also auger shell.
A going out of the way; a digression. [Obs.] Fuller.
One of the Trematodea. Also used adjectively.

To indulge one's self; to gratify one's tastes or desires;esp., to give one's self up (to); to practice a forbidden orquestionable act without restraint; -- followed by in, but formerly,also, by to. "Willing to indulge in easy vices." Johnson.

An equilateral parallelogram, or quadrilateral figure whosesides are equal and the opposite sides parallel. The angles may beunequal, two being obtuse and two acute, as in the cut, or the anglesmay be equal, in which case it is usually called a square.
A narrow stripe of purple worn by the equites on each side ofthe tunic as a sign of rank.
